  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Fon.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Also at 3rd level, you learn to strike with deadly efficiency, blending deadly poison with your fighting. Piercing damage you deal also counts as Poison damage for the purposes of interacting with jutsu, features, and traits, as well as overcoming Resistances and Immunities and capitalizing on Vulnerabilities.</p><p>Also, once per round when you make a weapon attack or cast a Taijutsu or Bukijutsu that deals Piercing or Poison damage using a weapon with the Unarmed property, you can force affected creatures to make a Constitution or Charisma Saving Throw vs your Taijutsu Save DC.</p><p>On a failure, they gain 1 rank of Envenomed and then take the damage of their Envenomed condition. If a creature fails their saving throw by 5 or more, they instead gain two ranks.</p><p>At 7th level, this can occur up to twice per round. If a creature that has three or more ranks of Envenomed fails this feature's saving throw, they take your weapon's damage in Poison damage on a failure, or half as much on a success.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
